  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In other words, the, the, the genocide and the preparation for the genocide is really driven by a bureaucracy.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We just execute laws.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In fact, in subsequent legal actions that have to deal with some of the recovery of our property, you know, from a legal standpoint, the thing is legitimate because even America recognized the acts of law passed by the Slovak government.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, it's a legitimate government.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It has a-- it has a legislature.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The courts approve it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The courts review the decisions.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And you fill out the forms.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And you have no recourse.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So it is this understanding how the machinery of the state can be used to sort of strip people out of existence which becomes a very significant influence on my outlook.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Much of the Holocaust [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] discussion deals with out-and-out brutal beating, shooting, murder, and what have you.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There has been very little given in terms of documentation of what proceeded that process, where the machinery of the police state, in fact, starts preparing people for the Final Solution.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And it's done in a very deliberate, studied, and organized way,",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Always the key being incrementally so that it's almost imperceptible at some point.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In addition to that, in addition to that, what is interesting, the state always sees to it that there are people who have become stakeholders of this thing.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So when you decide that you cannot live on [NON-ENGLISH], the immediate issue is, well, who is going to move into these Jewish houses?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father saw to it that I had private tutors.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In fact, I must say that my education in 1940 and '41 particularly greatly improved.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
